els100SysSerialno.name: els100SysSerialno
els100SysSerialno.description: The serial number of the system.

els100SysTftpIPAddress.name: els100SysTftpIPAddress
els100SysTftpIPAddress.description: The IP address of the TFTP server from which a software download is to be initiated. This variable must be set before a TFTP download can be started with the els100SysTftpStartDownload variable.

els100SysTftpFilename.name: els100SysTftpFilename
els100SysTftpFilename.description: The name of the software upgrade file residing on the TFTP server. Path information must be included in the file name. This variable must be set before a TFTP download can be started with the els100SysTftpStartDownload variable.

els100SysPowerupCount.name: els100SysPowerupCount
els100SysPowerupCount.description: The total number of times the system has powered up since it was shipped from the factory.

els100SysBrcastCutoffRate.name: els100SysBrcastCutoffRate
els100SysBrcastCutoffRate.description: The Broadcast Cutoff Rate of the switch allowing for the control of broadcast storms. The value of this variable sets a per second rate. If the broadcast and unknown destination address frames being forwarded through the system surpass this rate, they are dropped. Valid values for this parameter are in the range (100..500000).

els100SysGatewayIPAddress.name: els100SysGatewayIPAddress
els100SysGatewayIPAddress.description: The IP address of the next hop router (gateway) to which frames destined for an IP subnet different than what the system resides are sent.

els100SysTftpStartDownload.name: els100SysTftpStartDownload
els100SysTftpStartDownload.description: Start a TFTP download. A SET of this variable with the value download (1) initiates a TFTP download to upgrade the system software. The variables els100SysTftpIPAddress and els100SysTftpFilename must be configured before a download can begin. A GET of this variable will always return the value noDownload (2).

els100SysBootPDhcpEnable.name: els100SysBootPDhcpEnable
els100SysBootPDhcpEnable.description: Enable or disable the operation of the BootP and DHCP protocols on the system. These protocols are used for automatically configuring the system's IP address information if a properly configured BootP and/or DHCP server exists on the network.

els100SysReset.name: els100SysReset
els100SysReset.description: Initiate a software reset of the system.

els100SysSyslogServer.name: els100SysSyslogServer
els100SysSyslogServer.description: The IP address of the Syslog Server.

els100SysLowestSyslogSeverity.name: els100SysLowestSyslogSeverity
els100SysLowestSyslogSeverity.description: The Lowest Syslog Severity Level. All logs with the same or higher severity will be delivered. Note: higher severity has lower number.

els100SysComPortEnable.name: els100SysComPortEnable
els100SysComPortEnable.description: The administrative state of the Com Port.

els100PortEntry.name: els100PortEntry
els100PortEntry.description: An entry in the port table.

els100Port.name: els100Port
els100Port.description: The number of the port, from 1 to the number of ports on the system.

els100PortStatus.name: els100PortStatus
els100PortStatus.description: The connection (link) status of the port, either up (linked) or down (not linked).

els100PortDuplexStatus.name: els100PortDuplexStatus
els100PortDuplexStatus.description: The duplex status of the port, either half duplex or full duplex.

els100PortForwardedFrames.name: els100PortForwardedFrames
els100PortForwardedFrames.description: The number of frames received on the port and forwarded to another port on the system module for processing.

els100PortRcvdLocalFrames.name: els100PortRcvdLocalFrames
els100PortRcvdLocalFrames.description: The number of frames received where the destination is on the port.

els100PortName.name: els100PortName
els100PortName.description: A descriptive string of up to 60 characters used by the network administrator to name the port.

els100PortEnable.name: els100PortEnable
els100PortEnable.description: The enable status of the port, either enable or disable.

els100PortSpeed.name: els100PortSpeed
els100PortSpeed.description: The speed the port is operating at: 10Mbps, or 100Mbps, or 1000Mbps.

els100PortAutonegEnable.name: els100PortAutonegEnable
els100PortAutonegEnable.description: The auto-negotiation status of the port, either enable or disable. When in the enable (2) state, the port will automatically configure its duplex and speed operation.

els100PortFlowControlEnable.name: els100PortFlowControlEnable
els100PortFlowControlEnable.description: The state of flow control operation of the port, either enable or disable.

els100SwitchIPAddress.name: els100SwitchIPAddress
els100SwitchIPAddress.description: The IP address of the system.

els100SwitchSubnetMask.name: els100SwitchSubnetMask
els100SwitchSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of the system.

els100ActiveAgingTime.name: els100ActiveAgingTime
els100ActiveAgingTime.description: The aging time of entries in the MAC address forwarding table of the system.

els100SwitchSTPStatus.name: els100SwitchSTPStatus
els100SwitchSTPStatus.description: The Spanning Tree status of the system, enter on or off.

els100SwitchTrapRcvr1.name: els100SwitchTrapRcvr1
els100SwitchTrapRcvr1.description: The IP address of the first SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapCommunity1.name: els100SwitchTrapCommunity1
els100SwitchTrapCommunity1.description: The community name of the first SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapRcvr2.name: els100SwitchTrapRcvr2
els100SwitchTrapRcvr2.description: The IP address of the second SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapCommunity2.name: els100SwitchTrapCommunity2
els100SwitchTrapCommunity2.description: The community name of the second SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapRcvr3.name: els100SwitchTrapRcvr3
els100SwitchTrapRcvr3.description: The IP address of the third SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapCommunity3.name: els100SwitchTrapCommunity3
els100SwitchTrapCommunity3.description: The community name of the third SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapRcvr4.name: els100SwitchTrapRcvr4
els100SwitchTrapRcvr4.description: The IP address of the fourth SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchTrapCommunity4.name: els100SwitchTrapCommunity4
els100SwitchTrapCommunity4.description: The community name of the fourth SNMP manager to which traps from the system are directed.

els100SwitchPortMirroringStatus.name: els100SwitchPortMirroringStatus
els100SwitchPortMirroringStatus.description: The Port Mirroring status of the system, either disable or enable.

els100SwitchMirroredPort.name: els100SwitchMirroredPort
els100SwitchMirroredPort.description: The port that is being mirrored - the source.

els100SwitchMirroringPort.name: els100SwitchMirroringPort
els100SwitchMirroringPort.description: The port that is mirroring - the destination.

els100SwitchXmitMirrorEnable.name: els100SwitchXmitMirrorEnable
els100SwitchXmitMirrorEnable.description: Enable or disable the mirroring of transmitted traffic out the mirrored port to the mirroring port.

els100SwitchRcvMirrorEnable.name: els100SwitchRcvMirrorEnable
els100SwitchRcvMirrorEnable.description: Enable or disable the mirroring of received traffic into the mirrored port to the mirroring port.

els100SwitchVlanEnable.name: els100SwitchVlanEnable
els100SwitchVlanEnable.description: Globally enable or disable the VLAN operation of the system.

els100SwitchVlanEntry.name: els100SwitchVlanEntry
els100SwitchVlanEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN configuration table.

els100SwitchVlanId.name: els100SwitchVlanId
els100SwitchVlanId.description: The number of the VLAN, from 1 to the number of VLAN's supported on the system.

els100SwitchVlanName.name: els100SwitchVlanName
els100SwitchVlanName.description: A descriptive string of up to 60 characters used by the network administrator to name the VLAN.

els100SwitchVlanPorts.name: els100SwitchVlanPorts
els100SwitchVlanPorts.description: The set of ports in the VLAN. For systems supporting tagged VLAN's, these are the ports to which packets on the VLAN are sent untagged. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus each port of the system is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the VLAN; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

els100SwitchVlanEgressPorts.name: els100SwitchVlanEgressPorts
els100SwitchVlanEgressPorts.description: The set of ports defined to be on other VLAN's to which tagged packets destined for this specific VLAN should also be sent. Thus, this variable defines ports on the system that reach stations downstream which are on this VLAN and to which traffic may be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus each port of the system is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the VLAN; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

els100SwitchVlanStatus.name: els100SwitchVlanStatus
els100SwitchVlanStatus.description: Control variable used to enable or disable the operation of the associated VLAN in the system.

els100SwitchVlanPortEntry.name: els100SwitchVlanPortEntry
els100SwitchVlanPortEntry.description: An entry in the VLAN port configuration table.

els100SwitchVlanPortId.name: els100SwitchVlanPortId
els100SwitchVlanPortId.description: The number of the port, from 1 to number of ports in the system.

els100SwitchVlanPvid.name: els100SwitchVlanPvid
els100SwitchVlanPvid.description: The port's VLAN ID. For tagged VLAN's, this variable defines a 12 bit port VLAN ID (PVID) used as the identifier of the VLAN in the packet tag.

els100SwitchVlanPortType.name: els100SwitchVlanPortType
els100SwitchVlanPortType.description: For tagged VLAN's, the VLAN port type, either hybrid or access. Hybrid ports allow both tagged and untagged packets to enter the switch. Access ports only accept untagged packets.

els100SwitchPriorityEnable.name: els100SwitchPriorityEnable
els100SwitchPriorityEnable.description: Globally enable or disable the Class of Service traffic priority mechanism for the system.

els100SwitchPriorityThreshold.name: els100SwitchPriorityThreshold
els100SwitchPriorityThreshold.description: The global priority threshold level for the system at which VLAN tagged frames entering the associated port are assigned a high priority. This variable can have a value from (0...7). Traffic with a priority level equal to or above this value are high priority. Traffic with a priority level below this value are normal priority.

els100SwitchPriorityPortEntry.name: els100SwitchPriorityPortEntry
els100SwitchPriorityPortEntry.description: An entry in the port priority table.

els100SwitchPriorityPortId.name: els100SwitchPriorityPortId
els100SwitchPriorityPortId.description: The port number, from 1 to number of ports in the system.

els100SwitchPriorityDefault.name: els100SwitchPriorityDefault
els100SwitchPriorityDefault.description: The port priority level assigned to untagged traffic entering the associated port. This variable can have a value in the range (0...7). This value is compared to the value of the els100SwitchPriorityThreshold variable to determine if the traffic on the port is high or normal.

els100SwitchSpanningTreeStandby.name: els100SwitchSpanningTreeStandby
els100SwitchSpanningTreeStandby.description: Globally enable or disable Spanning Tree Standby. If set to disable, every port will instanly enter forwarding mode after link up
